The paper proposes an automated system for classifying lung nodules in CT images, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of different linear and non-linear discriminant classifiers suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for image classification is also possible, which would place the paper in the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it involves the analysis and classification of medical images for diagnostic purposes.
